args:
The battle against time-wielding Chronos proves
difficult, but when Vania receives the blood of
her future self, she awakens to overwhelming
power. Her new might sees Chronos's plot
foiled, and peace returns once more.
Fool... My flesh is unending.\nMy time is without bound.
Damn thing's near fully healed again!\nWhat do we gotta do to KILL it?!
I would advise you to cast your idle hopes\naside. As long as I command this power,\nvictory is forever beyond your grasp.
Even the unlikely return of your Tuner\nfriend would change nothing.
Then why were you so eager to stop me?\nPerhaps because you lack the confidence\nto back your boasting?
I've kept you overlong, my confederate.\nI return bearing the font of life, drawn from\nshe who rules in darkness in times distant.
Great! Still have absolutely no idea what\nthose words mean in that order, but I'm\nguessing you got Vania's blood?
Grimnir, quickly. Administer it to Vania!
Correct. The dragon you named Malinda\nsleeps alongside your brethren at the\nheart of these woods.
Correct again. I must thank you for being\nso eagerly deceived. It made my work far\neasier.
I had hoped to repay that kindness by\nending this before you woke. Alas, it\nseems a painless death is not to be.
You won't get away with this...\nYou know I get really scary when I'm mad!
Your waking was a small miscalculation.\nNow I've no choice but to whittle down that\nnear-boundless life of yours until y—RGK?!
I told you not to make me mad.
Still! You may be able to bind a low-\nlevel fiend as you are now, but...?!
This is why you so feared the princess of\nyour own world, is it not? Then you really\noughtn't to have given me free rein.
Would it clarify the situation if I told you\nthe blood I ferried back came not from the\npast, but the distant future?
Rgh... Damnable conductor! You used the\nblood of the awakened princess—of the\nvampire queen herself!
I'm feeling SUPER strong and SUPER\nout of patience for you, buster!
Nrgh... WROOOAUGH?! Was her power\ntruly so vast...? My strength...fades...!
I can't forgive what you've done...but I\nalso won't forget that you stayed by my\nside when I was at my loneliest.
I was sweatin' for a minute there,\nbut I guess it all worked out in the end.
Yes, thanks to all of you. I am sorry\nto have put us all through that.
Would you stop talking about it like it's all\nyour fault, {player_name}?
Yeah! If we're dishing out blame, I'm\nputting all of it on that no-good dragon!\nHe better hope he never sees ME again!
Perhaps you're right... In any case, it's true\nthat everything turned out all right thanks\nto all of you.
Especially Grimnir. We would have been\npowerless to stop Chronos without his aid.
I wish I could have thanked him properly,\nbut he just said something about his task\nas a Tuner being complete and vanished.

I'm still not clear on who the heck that
guy even was. Something about causality
and time and guardians? Sounds fake,
but okay.
True, he was an enigmatic figure. It seems\nhe's a part of some larger structure beyond\nthe limits of the world we know.
I was curious about that myself. I would\nbe eager to learn more, should our paths\ncross again.
Be kinda awkward, after his parting quip\nabout how ＂the threads of our fates shall\nne'er interweave again (nailed it!).＂
If they wanted me to stick around here with\nthe prince awhile, you'd REALLY think they\ncould have said so earlier.
Now I'm gonna look like a complete tool...\nWhy'd I have to go with THAT line?
Okay, what's my move here? Do I go full\ndramatic reunion? Keep it casual with a\n＂we meet again＂?! Decisions, decisions...
He's...been like that this whole time.
He's totally lost in his own weird, cringey\nlittle world. Doesn't even notice me.
Ooh, what if I just hid? That could work.
Then, if the prince is in danger, I can jump\nin with a breezy, ＂I could scarce allow my\nsworn brother to come to harm!＂
Awkward... I'd really rather you just\nwalked in through the front door.
Oh, come on, that's WAY too boring for—\nNWAAAUGH?! Prince?!
Er... It's been too long, my compatriot. The,\nuh... The winds of fate have guided me\nonce more to, um...blow here to your side.
Meaning, my boss told me I had to help\nyou out so can I please crash at your house\nfor a while please and thanks?
Your ＂boss...＂ As in, the keeper of fate\nand causality? I may not understand the\nspecifics, but your aid is most welcome.
Leave all to me! The wind shall be your\ninexhaustible quiver and adamant shield,\nwings fit to bear you to heights untold!
...So, uh. Yeah. Guess I live here now.\nThanks, roomie.
It is I who should thank you.
Now, tell me of the vampire princess.\nHow does she fare? Has she returned\nto the heart of the forbidden wood?
I'm booored. Come play hide-and-seek\nwith me!
Vania... {player_name} is terribly\nbusy. Perhaps you could see if any of the\nvillagers want to—
No way! I want to play with HIM!
And he's my bloodkin, so it's his job to\nmake sure I never feel lonely or bored\never again!
Yeesh... So yeah, you can see for yourself.
(The keeper said that the prince of this\nworld is different from that of any other...)
(Was this crossing of his fate with that of\nthe vampire princess due to that? Or...)
